6: Well, aren't you a sight for sore eyes.
10:
You summoned me? Undoubtedly
for another twisted scheme?
14: Twisted is such a harsh word.
18:
Just last week, a number of pirate
crews found themselves shipless.
Now, the coastal city where they
sought refuge is attempting to sell
off its governing rights.
26:
Now, now. I would never manipulate
the market. Though I admit it was an
attractive locale, so I secured the
purchase.
30:
I regret only one thing: there is not a
single cute soul within the city.
34:
You're worried about what your new
citizens LOOK like?
38:
Of course not. I was concerned that
my new little gum drops wouldn't
require my protection. They would
never ask me with their full hearts
for my patronage.
40:
And yet—realizing I own their labor,
the way they hang their heads in
utter hopelessness—I could not
resist!
44:
Spare me the details, please. What
are you going to do with your new
pets?
48:
I was thinking, perhaps, I should exile
them all.
51:
My city should be a place for only
the adorable to congregate. Where
cuteness is produced and
displaced. And it will all be for my
benefit...
54: If you think I will allow such a—
57:
(No... Antagonizing her would
accomplish nothing... Gods above,
forgive me for what I'm about to do!)
70: I think that you will be a superb ruler!
76:
You have ideas like no one else I've
ever encountered! Such as this
very... streamlined city plan!
80:
So, well... I think you should go
through with it! With my assistance!
We'll manage the city affairs hand in
hand!
89:
Don't flounder! Get your fresh fish
here! Cheap as gills!
91:
Coral handicrafts! Serving you
perfect seaside souvenirs!
95:
This is amazing! I've never seen such
an active harbor! You can
accomplish anything if you set your
mind to it!
99:
I merely gave them fishing rights
and a ship.
102:
Labor is the power that drives the
market. These crooks just needed to
be made into laborers, and the rest
took care of itself.
106:
You make it sound like it was easy...
Thank goodness you actually
listened to my advice.
109:
Indeed. You didn't garner an inch of
height, but even I can see that
you've grown by this experience.
113:
I, too, once fraternized with my
superiors, hiding my true intentions
from them. Ahh, such good
memories.
122:
One note: your confident façade is
lacking. You would curry more of my
favor by acting distraught.
127:
H-how dare you! That kind of deceit
is beneath me!
132:
I suppose so. We're cut from
different cloth. But that's why I loved
your little experiment here.
135:
You went through so much trouble
to trick me. How your heart must
have been beating, worrying that I
would find out.
138:
This whole time, I've completely
monopolized your thoughts. And I
couldn't be happier.
146:
Let's... Let's continue the tour! We still
haven't sampled all the stalls!
150:
After you. I would LOVE to see these
samples we missed.
159: Oh, Light. You are so precious.
164:
I am NOT precious! I am strong and
noble!
